Test cricket Under Dhoni's captaincy, India topped the Test cricket rankings for the first time, in 2009.[176] Dhoni has the most overseas Test defeats by an Indian captain, with 15.[177][178][179] Dhoni is the first Indian wicket-keeper to complete 4,000 Test runs.[180] Dhoni's maiden century against Pakistan in Faisalabad (148) is the fastest century scored by an Indian wicket-keeper, and fourth overall.[181] After hitting a six in the third Test against England in Southampton, Dhoni completed 50 sixes as a captain, an Indian record.[182] Dhoni, with 294 dismissals in his career, ranks first in the all-time dismissals list by Indian wicket-keepers.[183] Dhoni shares the record for most dismissals in an innings (6, with Syed Kirmani) and in a match (9) by an Indian wicket-keeper.[184] Dhoni is first Indian wicket-keeper to score 300 runs and take 15 dismissals in a series.[185] ODI cricket See also: List of players who have scored 10,000 or more runs in One Day International cricket Dhoni is third captain (and the first non-Australian) overall to win 100 games.[186] Fourth Indian to reach 10,000 ODI runs after Sachin Tendulkar, Sourav Ganguly & Rahul Dravid and also the second wicket-keeper to reach the milestone.[187] First player to pass 10,000 runs in ODI cricket with having a career average of over 50.[188] Dhoni has the fifth highest batting average (51.09), among cricketers with more than 5,000 runs and the second highest batting average among players with an aggregate of over 10,000 runs.[189] Most career runs in ODI history when batting at number 6 position (4031).[190] Only player to score more than one hundred in ODI cricket when batting at number 7 position or lower (Dhoni has 2 centuries at number 7).[191] Most not outs (84) in ODIs.[192] First Indian and fifth overall to hit 200 sixes in ODIs.[193] Dhoni's 183* against Sri Lanka in 2005 is the highest score by a wicket-keeper.[194] Dhoni's 113 against Pakistan in Chennai in 2012 is the highest by a captain batting at number 7.[195] Dhoni and Bhuvneshwar Kumar were involved in a partnership of 100 not out against Sri Lanka, which is India's highest eighth wicket partnership in ODIs.[196] Most unbeaten innings and highest average (among batsmen with more that 20 such innings) in successful ODI run-chases.[197] Holds the record for playing the most matches in ODI history as captain who has also served as a wicket-keeper(200).[198] Dhoni holds the records of the most dismissals in an innings (6) and career (432) by an Indian wicket-keeper.[199] Dhoni has the most stumpings (120) by any wicket-keeper in an ODI career also in an innings (3) and is so far the only keeper to pass 100 stumpings.[200][201] First Indian wicket-keeper to take 300 ODI catches and fourth wicket-keeper in the world to achieve the feat.[202] T20I Cricket Most matches as captain in T20Is(72)[203] Most matches in T20I history as both captain and wicket-keeper (72)[204] Most consecutive T20I innings without a duck (84)[205] Dhoni holds the record for playing the most T20I innings (76) and scored the most runs(1,153) before scoring a fifty[206][207][208] Most dismissals as wicket-keeper in T20Is (87)[209] Most catches as wicket-keeper in T20Is (54)[210] Most stumpings as wicket-keeper in T20Is (33)[209] Most catches as wicket keeper in a T20I innings (5)[211] Combined ODI, Test and T20I He has played the most international matches as captain (332)[212] Dhoni is the first, and so far only, wicket-keeper to effect 150 stumping dismissals across the three forms of the game. His current total of stumpings in internationals stands at 161[213][214]
